outlined.description: Styles the autocomplete as an outlined text field. (`label` or `placeholder` required)

source.description: Defines the data to use, must be specified.

input-id.description: The id attribute of the <input> and the for attribute of the <label>.

label.description: A text caption or description for the autocomplete, which use the input's `placeholder` attribute instead.

disabled.description: Styles the autocomplete as a disabled text field.

required.description: Styles the autocomplete as a required text field.

autofocus.description: If set to `true` the first item will automatically be focused when the menu is shown.

delay.description: The delay in milliseconds between when a keystroke occurs and when a search is performed. A zero-delay makes sense for local data (more responsive), but can produce a lot of load for remote data, while being less responsive.

minlength.description: The minimum number of characters a user must type before a search is performed. Zero is useful for local data with just a few items, but a higher value should be used when a single character search could match a few thousand items.

remote.description: Get data by AJAX. Default usage for local data.

highlight.description: Styles the autocomplete suggestion value as a strong text.

fullwidth.description: Styles the autocomplete as a full width text field.

end-aligned.description: Styles the autocomplete with an end-aligned input.

icon.description: Indicates an icon element with a leading icon.

with-leading-icon.description: Styles the autocomplete as a text field with a leading icon.

with-trailing-icon.description: Styles the autocomplete as a text field with a trailing icon.
